Volleyball Update for parents, guardians, players, coaches!
Park Rapids volleyball will be conducting practice during the MSHSL Fall Training Sessions. We will run practices from Monday, September 14th through Friday, September 25th for grades 7-12 from 3:30 - 5:00. 7th and 8th grade will be at the Century Middle School and 9-12 will be at the High School. You will need to go to the school website and register to participate. Here is the link:

ALSO,
There will be Panther Volleyball Clinic for grades 3-6 on Monday, September 28th - Wednesday September 30th in the Century Middle School gym. Volleyball players in grades 10-12 will help run that clinic.

Independent School District No. 309
Park Rapids, MN 56470

POSITION TITLE:
FOOD SERVICE SUBSTITUTE

POSITION PURPOSE: Produce and serve a variety of nutritionally balanced food prepared by using tested and uniform recipes to students, staff, and visitors.

TRAINING & EXPERIENCE:

MINIMUM EDUCATION OR EXPERIENCE: High School Diploma or GED.

LICENSE NEEDS: None.

SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS:
Ability to obtain Fundamentals of Health and Sanitation of School Food Nutrition Certificate with one year of employment.
Must be able to lift and manage 40 lbs of weight.
Computer skills may be needed and are strongly desired.

IMMEDIATE SUPERVISOR: Food Service Supervisor

Apply online on the District website at:
https://www.applitrack.com/parkrapids/onlineapp/

Park Rapids Community,
The following is what the Minnesota State High School League decided on for Fall Sports..

Fall Sports Approved: (Starting August 17th)
Cross Country-Limited to 3 teams per event
Girls Tennis - Limited to 2 teams per event (no invites)
Girls Swimming- Limited to 2 teams per event (no invites)

Fall Sports moved to Spring: (Starting tentatively Mid-March)
Volleyball-shortened schedules, no scrimmages, modified playoffs
Football- shortened local schedules, no scrimmages, modified playoffs

Spring Sports will be moved to a summer schedule from May until early July

üöÉ Substitute Bus Drivers Needed üöÉ

Park Rapids School District 309 is looking for Substitute Bus Drivers to provide safe and efficient transportation for District students to and from school.

MINIMUM EDUCATION OR EXPERIENCE; High School Diploma, equivalent, or other successful job-related experience, skill, or training.
LICENSE NEEDS; CDL License with Passenger, Air Brake and School Bus Endorsement required.
SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS; Must be able to pass a DOT Physical. CPR and First Aid Training recommended and desired.
Please contact Cindy Leach at 218-237-6570 or Human Resources, Marie Skoblik at 218-237-6508.
You may also apply online at the Park Rapids School website under the Human Resources tab, click the Application Link

post_text:
IMPORTANT TRANSPORTATION NOTICE!

ATTENTION PARENTS: Transportation is starting to plan for fall routes and we really need your help! With the changes that have occurred with Co-Vid and the current recommendations from Minnesota Dept of Education, we need to know your plans for the coming school year.

Are you still planning to have your student(s) ride the school bus to/from school? In our attempt to keep your children safe, we will more than likely be instituting a one bus assignment for your child. We are going to make our best attempt to keep your children safe and social distanced from other children. Please communicate your transportation plans so that we can assess the need for additional bus routes and seating on these buses.

You can call (218)237-6570, or email cleach@parkrapids.k12.mn.us.

We really appreciate your help on this!

post_text:
The Hunt Is On!

Good Morning - PRAHS!!!!

It is Tuesday, April 13th and the hunt is on! You have a week to find as many #WorldofHearts and #BetheLight displays as you can.

The quest is simple - see a display, make a tally. Turn in the total number of displays you found to either Mrs. Schroeder or Mrs. Walsh by Tuesday, April 21st. Take a picture of the display you like the most and send it to either Mrs. Schroeder or me by Tuesday, April 21st. You cannot pick your own.

The displays can be on public buildings, businesses or private residences.

Remember - the goal is to get out of the house, practice social distancing and see the support in our community.

Still want to make a display? It is not too late, pick your spot (door, window, lawn,etc) be creative and get to work. There is still time!

Hope you had a good Easter weekend and ready to get back to work!

#WorldofHearts/#BetheLight,
Shelli R. Walsh

We had a great first day of Distance Learning at all levels. Staff and students alike had the feel of beginning a new year. I am proud of the Park Rapids Area Schools, families and community in all their work to make our Distance Learning Plan successful for students.

Reminder:

If you have a question or need assistance regarding technology, email: techsupport@parkrapids.K12.mn.us
Did you know‚Ä¶ The Park Rapids Area HS pool holds 185,000 gallons of water.

As always, if you have questions or comments please call me or one of the school offices.

Thank you,

Lance Bagstad

At Century Elementary we have been working on keeping our school a kind place to be. Every month our classroom teachers read a book pertaining to kindness, positive choices, acceptance, persistence or empathy. After hearing the story, the students are asked to write about the topic of the book.
Theme: Positive Choices
The Bad Seed by Jory John
This book is about a bad seed. A baaaaaaaad seed. How bad? Do you really want to know? He has a bad temper, bad manners and a bad attitude. He's been bad since he can remember! This seed cuts in line every time, stares at everybody and never listens. But what happens when one mischievous little seed changes his mind about himself, and decides that he wants to be- happy?

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MtozACAsNLQ

Pride stands for:
P - positive
R - respectful
I - incredible
D - dedicated
E - effort

Congratulations Students and keep up the great work!

post_text:
More photos from the music contest!

The Park Rapids music department had a strong showing at High School League ensemble contest Monday. All of our groups earned Superior or Excellent ratings, the top 2 levels.

Receiving excellent ratings:

The brass ensemble of Ethan Hemmenwsy, Sophia Guida, Alex Hensel, Levi Trygstad, Mary Nichols, and Isaac Knapp.

The trombone duet of Alex Hensel and Grace Litzau.

The clarinet quartet of Kaelie Olson, Rian Soderberg, Natalie Backmann, and Louisa Etter.

Receiving Superior ratings:

The vocal Duet of Jon Wormer and Kamree Carlson.

The vocal Duet of Johnna Krabenhoft and Alicia Heath.

The flute and oboe quartet of Maria Wagner, Jillian Nuebauer, Faith Hepola, and Maeve Bolton.

The percussion quartet of Bode Lee, Keegan Moses, Kiergon Wilkins and Alan Guajardo.

The Clarinet Duet of Em & Jon Wormer.

The Flute/Clarinet Duet of Maria Wagner and Em Worner.

Congrats to all of our ensembles for performing well and representing Park Rapids with pride!

Our first ever ‚ÄúPanthers First: Career Exploration Community Mentoring Program‚Äù
was a great success! 35 Career Mentors, covering many career clusters, were present along with the Junior and Senior classes.
It was a great time to be able to have casual conversations with career professionals to learn about careers and about our town, networking and building relationships, as well as guiding students on a path that they can be passionate about and to get to know their strengths.

We want to give a BIG Thank You to all of our Community Career Mentors on making this program possible!

We are so excited to say there is more to come in March & April.

post_text:
Middle School Monthly Letter for Parents
From Sherri:

Hello parents,

I hope everyone is enjoying the Winter Break.

Here is some important dates for January:

1/2- return to school from break

1/8- 5-8 Conferences from 3:30-7:00

Conferences will be held only on Wednesday, January 8 from 3:30-7:00. If you are not able to make this date, your child's teacher will be reaching out to you either by phone or email.

1/20- Middle School band concert for grades 6-12 at 7:00 at Century Gym

1/22- Early Out, students are dismissed at 1:00

If you do not have a ParentVue account, please contact me and I will help you get set up for one. Once you get it set up, you will have access to all your children's grades, classes, etc.

We have a new website! Check it out at www.parkrapids.k12.mn.us .

Lastly, PTA will be having their meeting on Monday, January 20th at 6:30. Hope you can join them.

Stay warm,

Sherri Gottsman

Administrative Assistant

Century Middle School

218-237-6300

Park Rapids Education & Activities Foundation - PREAF
November 25, 2019 at 10:04 AM ¬∑

A big thank you to RDO Frozen/Lamb Weston for their continued collaboration with the PREAF for our recent Community French Fry Sale. We are very thankful for their generous donation of potato products and transportation of products to the sale. And we are especially grateful to the community and to all those who attended and supported our event. Thank you to all who purchased potatoes, as all money raised from the sales goes directly to the PREAF and are allocated to educational, fine arts, and athletic programs in the Park Rapids Area Schools. Thank you to R&R Rental for your donation of your forklift for the entire day at the sale. And thank you to the many students, teachers, coaches, and parent volunteers who helped at the event. Everyone involved helped make it a very successful fundraiser for the PREAF.

post_text: Today is World Kindness Day! Your Century Kindness Club members are placing post-it notes with inspiring messages on student lockers, AND they will have a booth Wednesday morning in the commons area for kids to "Write a compliment, Give a compliment." Kids will be able to write a compliment on a piece of paper, place it in a jar, and then grab a compliment from another jar to give to a random student they see in the hall. Our Kindness Club members will be in the halls every morning this week handing out compliments!

The French Fry Sale has been a very popular event, that directly gives back to our community and provides financial benefits for our school.

post_text:
This is our very first "kindness club". Our club consists of 2 students from each 4th grade classroom.

Our mission:
1. To build self-esteem and raise school morale by showing every person at our school that he or she really can make a difference.
2. To bring everyone at our school together in a cooperative, caring way.
3. To change the world with kindness!

Our club members are willing and ready to spread as much kindness throughout our school and community as we can!
